## Objectives

1. **Ad-hoc PRD intake** ‚Äî From a short change request, produce a developer-approved Ad-Hoc PRD under `.sedea/operations/.../docs/` via **`ad-hoc-prd`** (not full **`author-prd`**).

2. **Bounded Master Plan** ‚Äî Scaffold and draft a Master Plan with **`master-planner`**, compute complexity score; **reject** dispatches when overall score **> 20** (‚â• 21) and recommend **`plan and deliver`**.

3. **PR breakdown only** ‚Äî On the Master Plan lane, run **`pr-breakdown`** inline only (no **`delivery-phases`** / **`phase-planner`**); allow **1‚Äì6** PR rows; expand PR plans with **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline.

4. **Standard implementation and ship** ‚Äî After inline **`pr-plan`** ¬ß5c **Start coding session**, the **Master Plan child lane** emits ¬ß5d **`AGENT_RUN_REQUEST_V1`** for **`coding-session`** (same contract as plan-and-deliver). Ship chain runs on the spawned **`coding-session`** lane: cut-point, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, optional plan-reconcile. **Forbidden:** redirecting ¬ß5d spawn to the Squad Leader because the leader does not spawn ship skills from ¬ß¬ß1‚Äì7.

5. **Squad Leader oversight** ‚Äî Leader lane runs planning spawns (¬ß¬ß1‚Äì7), tracks planning ledger, and ¬ß8 ship ledger via Mission Control host sync (same automation contract as plan-and-deliver ¬ß8 when host supports this mission slug).

