```

### 5. Create Master Plan via agent

- **Type:** Agent engagement and handover
- **execution:** spawned
- **Intent:** Draft Master Plan ¬ß¬ß1‚Äì5 and complexity score via **`master-planner`**.
- **Target agent role:** Master Plan agent
- **Assigned skill:** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/master-planner/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/master-planner/SKILL.md)
- **Inputs:** ¬ß4 seed (`seedBlock`, `featurePlanningTitle`, `prdRef`, `Parent: null`, `related: []`) compiled into spawn **`inputs`** per **`plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc`** ¬ß5 *Spawn preflight* ‚Äî when seed has **`Parent: null`**, spawn **`"parent": "null"`** (JSON string), **not** JSON `null`.
- **Expected output:** `outputs.masterPlanPath`, `outputs.complexityScore`, `outputs.complexityBand`, ledger fields, `outputs.continuationOwner`, `outputs.continuationStatus`.

**Spawn preflight (binding):** Before **`AGENT_RUN_REQUEST_V1`**, read **`planner/SKILL.md`** frontmatter and **`plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** ¬ß *Universal spawn preflight* (row **1b**). **`Parent: null`** in the ¬ß4 seed is semantic; spawn wire uses **`"parent": "null"`**. Paste-ready example: **`planner/SKILL.md`** ¬ß *Spawn contract*.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - **`complexityScore` > 20** (‚â• 21) ‚Üí USER_CHECKPOINT gate below ‚Äî **do not** continue ¬ß6 on this dispatch.
  - **`complexityScore` ‚â§ 20** and continuation active on Master Plan lane ‚Üí ¬ß6 ack on leader (auto-advance); Master Plan agent owns ¬ß6‚Äì¬ß7 inline.

USER_CHECKPOINT ‚Äî pick next step when Master Plan complexity exceeds this mission ceiling (score > 20).

**Complexity gate (binding):** Parse **`### Complexity score`** overall score from child outputs. Values **> 20** (‚â• 21) fail this mission's eligibility; **20 is in band**.

### 6. PR breakdown only (Master Plan lane)

- **Type:** Branching logic + simple skill execution (Master Plan agent lane ‚Äî not Squad Leader)
- **Intent:** Decompose Master Plan with **`pr-breakdown`** only; enforce **1‚Äì6** PR rows.
- **execution:** inline on Master Plan child lane
- **Inputs:** `outputs.masterPlanPath`, complexity score ‚â§ 20.
- **Expected output:** Master Plan ¬ß6 titled **`PR breakdown`** (not Delivery phases); PR list with 1‚Äì6 rows; `spawnedPlans` / ledger updates.
- **Next-step resolution:** PR list approved ‚Üí ¬ß7 per PR row. More than 6 PRs needed ‚Üí stop; recommend **`plan and deliver`**.

**Procedure (Master Plan agent)**

1. **Forbidden:** **`delivery-phases`**, **`phase-planner`**, or AskQuestion menu offering Delivery phases.
2. Load **`pr-breakdown`** inline with `routeLock: pr-breakdown` when skill supports it; otherwise skip route AskQuestion and proceed directly to **`pr-breakdown`**.
3. After **`pr-breakdown`**, verify PR count **‚â§ 6**; if skill draft exceeds 6, revise down or stop with scope message recommending **`plan and deliver`**.
4. Run **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline for each PR row (same as plan-and-deliver Master Plan lane when **`pr-breakdown`** path chosen).
5. When **`pr-plan`** reports **`readyForImplementation: true`**, **re-enter** inline **`pr-plan`** ¬ß5c on **this Master Plan lane** ‚Äî emit ¬ß5d **`coding-session`** spawn when the developer selects **Start coding session**; **do not** close the master-master-planner lane with prose redirect to Squad Leader.
6. Report planning handoff readiness per **`30_planning-target-resolution`** ¬ß *Planning readiness vs ship*.

**Squad Leader ¬ß6:** Acknowledge status only ‚Äî no decomposition menu on leader lane.

### 7. Planning closure ledger

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Track planning lanes and PR plans until terminal; then ¬ß8 ship oversight.
- **Inputs:** Child results from ¬ß5‚Äì¬ß6; `spawnedPlans`, `openLedgerEntries`.
- **Expected output:** Planning ledger closed; PR plans `readyForImplementation` when applicable.
- **Next-step resolution:** All planning entries terminal ‚Üí ¬ß8. Open planning work ‚Üí wait and ack.

Same ledger rules as plan-and-deliver ¬ß7, except **no phase-planner rows** and **max 6 PR plan** entries.

### 8. Ship cadence ledger and dispatch resolution

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Track detached **`coding-session`** ship progress; gate **`MC_DISPATCH_RESOLVED_V1`**.
- **Inputs:** Host-sync ship ledger messages; planning handoff signals.

**Detached branches** ‚Äî identical skill order to plan-and-deliver ¬ß8 detached table: **`coding-session`** ‚Üí before deploy **`deploy-walk`** ‚Üí **`pre-pr-review`** spawn ‚Üí **`create-pr`** ‚Üí **`pr-review`** ‚Üí post-merge cleanup ‚Üí after deploy **`deploy-walk`** ‚Üí explicit **`plan-reconcile`**. **Detached** means off the **Squad Leader** ¬ß¬ß1‚Äì7 protocol ‚Äî **`coding-session`** is still spawned from the **Master Plan child lane** via inline **`pr-plan`** ¬ß5d per **`planner/SKILL.md`** Step **7c** and *Resume / PR-expand handoff*.

**¬ß8 automation:** Same host-sync contract as plan-and-deliver ¬ß8 (*Mission Control host sync*) when the Mission Control host registers this mission slug; until then treat missing sync as a **mission gap** ‚Äî do not manual-paste Ship recap.

USER_CHECKPOINT ‚Äî approve dispatch resolution when planning and ship gates allow.

**Dispatch resolution:** Squad Leader proposes **`MC_DISPATCH_RESOLVED_V1`** when planning complete and ship rows closed (or planning-only close per plan-and-deliver ¬ß8 gates).

